The paper deals with the problem of computing the expected value of a function over Markov chains and Markov decision processes, which is a common topic in the sub-fields of game theory (cs.GT), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves the computation of maximum values, which is a common topic in the sub-field of data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper deals with decision-making processes, which is a common topic in the sub-field of control systems (cs.SY).
